Sorry, It is my fault.
Something wrong with my code.
I haven't copy the whole folder from local machine to docker image.
I only copy one edited python file.
Although I don't know the exact reason.
But it is not the problem with the local machine and docker.
It does **could run** in docker if I copy the whole folder from local machine to docker image.
